The 24-year old has been taken to hospital following the incident on Saturday night. CAPE TOWN - An alleged gang leader has been shot and injured during a shootout with police in Belhar, in Cape Town.The 24-year old has been taken to hospital following the incident on Saturday night.The police's Noloyiso Rwexana says a bystander has also sustained injuries. The suspect was shot in the leg and a firearm was seized. He is believed to be a known gang leader in the area. He has been taken to hospital under police guard. Meanwhile, it was discovered that a 14-year-old girl was, who was a bystander, sustained a gunshot wound. 